roles.char: Boy at Party Who Kisses Marie

title: Strangers in the Night
description: Coach Lubbock fumes over a note passed in his classroom that may shed light on a late-night rendezvous one of his daughters had with a boy.

title: She Works Hard for the Money
The Dinner Test
description: Before the girls can go on date, they have to bring them to the house for what is known as the dinner test. Wherein the Coach tries to make sure that their date is OK. And so far no one passes. And when one of them has a date with guy who is sure to fail, they find a guy who seems like the kind of guy who could pass the test. So they introduce him as the date and bring him for the test.

title: Coach's Court
description: When the fence railing was broken and placed back together poorly Coach decides to have what is known as "Coach's Court" to find out. He learns that it began when one of his boxers made obscene remarks toward Marie and J.R. got in his face telling him to knock it off. That's when the girls go see him and when he does it again Marie slugs him.

title: Zorro en el Gallinero
description: Father Hargis brings a young man from Spain to the Lubbocks, whom he hopes will join the school. He hopes seeing the Lubbock girls will entice him. They all think he doesn't speak English but he can but continues to let them think so. And all four girls make a move on him by getting someone who speaks Spanish to tell him they like him.

title: The Good, the Bad and the Ugly

roles.char: Boy at Dance 'The Good, the bad & the ugly'

title: Puberty Blues
description: Coach teaches the girls about not playing when there's no grass on the field. A very special episode.

title: Quarterback Sneak
description: The quarterback of the Coach's football team takes a liking to Wendy. And when it seems that he's not focused on the game, Coach lets them go out on a date, and gives them free reign to do what they want. But when they play their last game, Coach wants them to stop seeing each other. However, they don't want to.

title: That Championship Season
description: Thr football team is in the championship in great part to the team's quarterback. But when the coach grades a test he took and failed, he is not eligible to play in the game. So the coach has to decide if he should enforce the suspension cause if he does it could mean the game.

title: Poetic Justice
description: Connie develops a crush on her poetry professor. He asks her to go somewhere with him. When Coach learns of this he rushes off to get her.
